\\ slug away your worries 🐌

Slugging is not a new concept, in fact it’s an age-old practice of applying an occlusive like petrolatum, to allow for maximum absorption of the products applied on the skin 🧏🏾‍♀️ It creates a seal & prevents water from evaporating (TEWL) to increase hydration in the skin 💦

I’ve been doing it for a while & I kid you not, but it actually leaves my skin feeling softer, smoother & more nourished ✨ Because essentially it’s protecting the skin barrier, by preventing moisture loss, which is crucial for healthy, luminous, glowing skin.

😌 It’s actually super easy to do - do your skincare routine. After moisturizer, apply an occlusive product like the @cerave Healing Ointment or even @vaselineindia , as the last step of your PM routine 🌙 Leave it on over night & wash it in the morning. 

Stick to using hydrating + barrier strengthening products in your routine 🧱Slugging itself isn’t hydrating, it only keeps the moisture in, but it helps the other products penetrate better, making them more effective ‼️BUT avoid using any strong actives like a retinoid or chemical exfoliant (BHA / AHA) with it, because trapping that could increase it’s strength & may cause irritation. 

🤨 Before you ask - no it won’t clog your pores. Petrolatum can definitely feel greasy on oily & acne prone skin, but theres no evidence to show it clogs the pores 🍓Theoretically oily skin could use it BUT it’s best suited for those with normal to dry skin. As it involves occluding the skin, it could lead to acne if you are acne-prone or have oily skin, as sebum + acne-causing bacteria could get trapped into pores & cause inflammation / pimples 💩

Does everyone need to do this⁉️NO. But if you’re struggling with dryness, dehydrated skin or a damaged skin barrier, give it a go. Start with once a week & see how your skin feels after.

Have you ever tried slugging? Would you ever try it? Tell me in the comments👇🏽

\\ #ResetAndRelax @aveenoindia

Life is back in full swing (thank god for that 🙌🏽) & my schedule has been getting super busy. But with all the crazy going on, I make sure to take sometime out for myself everyday - & skincare time is my self care time 🧖🏽‍♀️

So I decided to take up the #ResetandRelax Challenge with @aveenoindia 💜

Here’s a simple routine i followed to give my self some extra love!

🏋🏻‍♀️Move my body & get in a workout (I like to push myself to try different things that take me out of my comfort zone)

🕯Slow down, light a scented candle & let the aroma soak in
3. Get into a nice warm bath with the @aveenoindia Soothing and Calming Body Wash. It’s gentle, hydrating & has scents of lavender, chamomile and Ylang Ylang to help me relax & wind down.

latestIgtvVideos.title: \\ Rolling away my worries 💩
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Waking up with a dull, tired & puffy face is never a good look - but we all have such days (leave a 🙋🏽‍♀️ if you have). An ice roller is my most trusted ‘device’ for an instant wake me 🆙. It helps me calm, de-puff and cool my drowsy face and It’s like a self-care ritual for me 😌
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
While ice rolling is great, some days my skin just needs an extra glow up ✨ The @renskincare Flash Rinse 1 Minute Facial - With Water Activated Vitamin C 🍊 is the quickest & most innovative mask I’ve tried. It has 10% Ascorbic Acid (the purest form of Vitamin C) that helps to brighten dull skin, evens out the skin tone, fights free-radicals & prevents fine lines + wrinkles 🧏🏾‍♀️ It also has a Magnesium oxygen complex + emollients that keep the skin radiant & soft after rinsing it off. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Watch the video to see how to activate the Vitamin C in the mask! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I love using this before an event or if my skin is looking a little blah 😑 It always makes my skin feel smoother & look more refreshed. But don’t expect to see magical results with one use. Vitamin C takes time to show any visible effect on the skin. Consistency + patience is 🔑. All skin types can benefit from this but it could be great option if you’re sensitive to stronger Vitamin C serums or if you love masks and are lazy like me ✌🏽

latestIgtvVideos.title: \\ Is it already November?! 🤯
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
These past 2 months have been crazy work wise and I haven’t been able to dedicate as much time to this page as I would like to 💩I feel guilty about it but I’m learning how to find a balance 🏗 I have so much to share with you all and I promise I will - just be patient 🙏🏽
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A month ago I posted my AM  routine ☀️ My skin was not in a very happy place then - it was just starting to heal from a massive acne outburst and I had a lot of pigmentation, scarring, blackheads & whiteheads to deal with. Since then I’ve been quite consistent with my routine. Kept it relatively simple. Focused on - hydrating, healing &  soothing - and it’s exactly what my skin needed 🙌🏽 I still have a long way to go BUT
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✨I have 0 active pimples right now
✨My skin barrier has repaired
✨The post inflammatory pigmentation is slowly healing
✨My skin’s been plump & dewy
✨I feel happier, more confident & less stressed
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ve also been reflecting on how I let the way my skin looks dictate my mood & how I feel about myself - it’s hard stay unaffected and not feel crappy. But I’m learning to think more positively - for my own mental sanity 🌈

Can you relate? How do you cope with bad skin days?👇🏽
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
